      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EL REY (7) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 30.56 beating ELDRITCH. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Looks to have an edge on most of these. FANTASTIC HELGA (1) copped a check in the run last time and never threatened when seventh (26.72) in a Grade 3/4/5 at this track. Rates a key player and gets chance to atone. CARUGGI (3) comes off an average effort last start when fifth at Angle Park over 530m behind Nola Keeping (31.52) in a Grade 3/4/5. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Key runner on best form. ELDRITCH (5) was strongly fancied last time on the back of some good form but finished second (30.61) at this track. Boasts a strong record from this draw with two wins and two minor placings from five starts. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win.",
